olive oil
1 packet green beans
1 head broccoli
1 packet Egg Noodles
1 packet pork mince
1 sachet Sweet Soy Seasoning
1 packet Katsu Paste
1 packet coconut milk
1 tsp soy sauce
¼ cup water
1 packet Coriander

• Boil the kettle.
• Trim green beans.
• Cut broccoli (including stalk!) into small florets.
• Half-fill a medium saucepan with boiling water. Cook egg noodles over medium-high heat, stirring occasionally with a fork to separate, until tender, 4-5 minutes.
• Drain, rinse and set aside.

• Meanwhile, heat a large frying pan over high heat with a drizzle of olive oil.
• Cook pork mince, green beans and broccoli, breaking up mince with a spoon, until just browned, 5-6 minutes.
• Add sweet soy seasoning and cook until fragrant, 1 minute.

• Reduce heat to medium, then add katsu paste, coconut milk, the soy sauce and water and simmer until slightly reduced, 2-3 minutes.
• Remove pan from heat, then add the egg noodles and stir to combine. Season with salt and pepper.

• Divide speedy katsu pork and broccoli egg noodles between bowls.
• Tear over coriander to serve. Enjoy!